  <summary>7/13/1995--Introduced.
Federal Land Management Agency Concession Reform Act of 1995 - Provides for a uniform concessions management policy for Federal land management agencies, including provisions regarding: (1) concession types; (2) public rates and charges; (3) concession transfers; (4) competitive selection; (5) concession fees; (6) private sector capital improvements; (7) creation of a Board of Concession Appeals; and (8) privatization of Forest Service and Bureau of Land Management lands subject to concession leases.</summary>
